1 IV. Any person who knowingly possesses a product in violation of paragraph I, II,
2 or III shall be guilty of a violation for a first through third offense, and a class B
3 misdemeanorforanyfourthorsubsequentoffense.
4 V. Any person who is convicted of violating paragraph I shall be subject to a fine of
5 $100 for a first or second offense,or a fine of up to $300 for any third or subsequent offense.
6 Theoffendershallforfeitthehemp-derivedproducttothestate.
7 VI. A corporation or unincorporated association shall be subject to a fine not to
8 exceed $20,000 for a misdemeanor and $1,000 for a violation. A writ of execution may be
9 issued by the court against the corporation or unincorporated association to compel
10 paymentofthefine,togetherwithcostsandinterest.
11 4 PremisesRestrictions;UnlawfulPurpose. AmendRSA179:50toreadasfollows:
12 179:50 UnlawfulPurpose.
13 I. No licensee shall use, or allow to be used, his or her premises for any purpose contrary to
14 law.
15 II. All licensees shall comply with the provisions of RSA 439-A:4 relative to certain
16 hemp-derivedproductscontainingTHCprohibited.
17 5 New Paragraph; Prohibited Sales. Amend RSA 179:5 by inserting after paragraph II the
18 followingnewparagraph:
19 III. No licensee, salesperson, nor any other person, shall sell or give away or cause or allow
20 or procure to be sold, delivered, or given away any product derived from hemp which contains
21 natural or synthetic tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) in any amount, which appear in any formulation,
22 including delta-8 THC, delta-9 THC, or any other THC isomer variant or tetrahydrocannabinolic
23 acid(THCA),toapersonundertheageof21.
24 6 EffectiveDate. ThisactshalltakeeffectJanuary1,2027.

